definition: (of water) to dash against/to mix with water/to infuse/to rinse/to flush/to develop (a film)/to rise in the air/to clash/to collide with
surname Yin/abbr. for 印度[Yin4 du4]
to print/to mark/to engrave/a seal/a print/a stamp/a mark/a trace/image

sentences.chinese: 你能夠沖印出很不錯的8x10規格的相片。

sentences.english: I sent three rolls of film away to be processed.
sentences.chinese: 我送了三個膠捲去沖印。

sentences.english: I was developing some pictures of a fence at the border and was listening to the radio at the same time.
sentences.chinese: 我一邊沖印有關邊境圍牆的照片，一邊收聽電臺廣播。

sentences.english: Photo shop programs have affected the kind of images the Alliance receives.
sentences.chinese: 相片沖印店的方案，影響了圖像的聯盟獲得一種。

sentences.english: You can get some at the drugstore or at the little photo printing shop around the corner.
sentences.chinese: 你可以在雜貨店買或在附近的小沖印店買。

sentences.english: At one point, he even donated blood for 75 yuan so he could develop his pictures.
sentences.chinese: 有一次，他竟然去獻血，換回75塊錢來沖印照片。

sentences.english: Our holiday photos haven't been developed yet.
sentences.chinese: 我們假日拍的照片還沒有沖印出來。

sentences.english: It had been seven years since it came into this world, born from the silvery solution of the photographic tray.
sentences.chinese: 這張照片從沖印盤的銀色溶液中誕生已經七年了。

sentences.english: The class pictures purchased by parents are now ready for distribution.
sentences.chinese: 班級照已沖印好等待被分發到家長的手中。
